# YouTube behavior
- YouTube scheduling:
  - Only set `status.publishAt` when `status.privacyStatus` is `private`.
  - `publishAt` must be an ISO-8601 timestamp and must be in the future.
- OAuth:
  - Store tokens only in main process (never renderer).
  - Implement refresh logic; handle expired/invalid tokens gracefully.
- Robustness:
  - Implement retry/backoff for transient network errors.
  - Return clear, actionable error messages to UI (no raw token dumps).
